textAfterTable: Tweets by @docomomo_us Hawaii Modernism Symposium Published by admin on Tue, 2011-12-27 15:41 Registration is now open for the upcoming Hawaii Modernism Symposium. Join Historic Hawai‘i Foundation for presentations, discussion and celebration of Hawaii’s significant architecture, planning and engineering achievements from the middle of the 20th century.  The event entitled: “Hawai‘i Modernism: a Symposium on Identification, Evaluation and Preservation of Our Recent Past” will be held Saturday, January 21, 2012, 8 a.m. – 3 p.m. at the East West Center in Honolulu.   The event will include a presentation of major findings from HHF’s recent context study on Hawai‘i Modernism, a national overview of Modernism, discussion groups on key issues nationally as well as locally and next steps. For additional details, visit the Historic Hawaii Foundation website or here for a flyer for the event. Before the main text Full width (900 pixels) Tags: SYMPOSIUM
